Ok, than i hear it like you do.  Isn&#39;t the idea of posting files to 
get different theories on what is heard?  What are we comprehending 
in these or any other files anyway?  We are just starting to break 
ground on full sentence answers, so we need to sift through them and 
make sense.  That one about the earthquake is a great file, but what 
does it mean???  It doesn&#39;t make any sense, we have to make sense of 
these files.  Whether it be in reverse, enhancing the audio or 
whatever.  This is our job as researchers, while they laugh their 
ass off on the other side watching us spend hours on the computer to 
say there is going to be an earthquake somewhere that doesn&#39;t 
happen.  If they say &quot;Steve likes cupcakes in a tree in east asia&quot;, 
that&#39;s a great file and it will be clear.  But what would it mean 
and what effect will it have on humanity.

Nuff Said&#39;
-Steve H.



